Much acclaim to my fellow travelbloggers from the US who have kayaked the English Channel or run marathons. I have to faint at the thought of that.

Relative to the rest of the world, long contracts are not as common in Australia, Europe or Japan. The personal commitment MOS incur in the States is much higher. The lack of understanding about the military bothers me.
It is human nature to believe your way is better not worse. Wrong. For a lot of folks, I agree that appearances aren’t everything. For soldiers, there should be a small amount of respect and courtesy. For example, if a coworker requests .8 duty, saying he needs to go to the car to get something, it may make a difference if the coworker was a cop, a firefighter or in the military. Civilians may think it’s an acceptable response, but that is totally disrespectful. I am not defending the military. It is stupid behavior. That coworker is simply stating where he needs to be in the nearest future to make it to work at the requested time (1 hour in most cases). Military folks
